Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.24,0:00:05.63,Episode Title,,0,0,0,,{\fade(255,0,255,0,1220,5000,5600)\pos(720,514)}Episode 27
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.24,0:00:05.63,Episode Title,,0,0,0,,{\fade(255,0,255,0,1220,5000,5600)\pos(720,787.999)}Three Visits to the Thatched Cottage
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.80,0:00:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,General, are you not {\i1}Liú of Yù-Province?{\i0} Do you wish to see my brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.98,0:00:39.64,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\fade(255,0,255,0,420,2200,2600)\pos(1268.861,607.038)}Zhūgě Jun
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.81,0:00:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,This way, General.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.85,0:00:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, take a seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.69,0:01:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,-This way. \N -After you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.73,0:01:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And sir, you are...?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.36,0:01:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I am the Sleeping Dragon's \Nyounger brother, {\i1}Zhūgě Jūn.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.64,0:01:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We are three brothers. My eldest is {\i1}Zhūgě Jǐn{\i0}, he is now an apparitor of{\i1} {\i0}Sūn Zhòngmóu in Jiangdong.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.36,0:01:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Kǒngmíng{\i0} is our middle brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.10,0:01:32.60,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\fade(255,0,255,0,420,5500,5920)\pos(192.52,729.583)}Liú Bèi \NStyled: Xuándé
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.38,0:01:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So, is the Sleeping Dragon at home today?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.42,0:01:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You've arrived too late, General.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.18,0:01:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,My brother went with Cuī Zhōupíng yesterday to wander.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.26,0:01:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And where did he go?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.62,0:01:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps he went sailing on the river on a small boat —
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.34,0:01:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,—or to visit Daoist priests \Nin the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.24,0:01:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Or else, gone to a village where his friend resides —
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.91,0:01:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,— or to play the{\i1} qin-{\i0}zither\N and weiqi in a mountain retreat.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.56,0:02:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,His journeys are unpredictable. I know not where he has gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.29,0:02:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems we weren't meant to meet each other after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.12,0:02:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Twice I came yet haven't encountered this virtuous man. How regrettable.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.40,0:02:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, sit for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.34,0:02:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Servant! Pour some tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.76,0:02:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother, the snow's falling fast. We better leave soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.32,0:02:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Since my brother isn't here, \NI dare not keep you any longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.95,0:02:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, I will visit again in a few days.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.94,0:02:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,May I borrow a brush and ink?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.24,0:02:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish to leave a letter to your brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.34,0:02:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring a brush and ink.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.72,0:02:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.91,0:03:05.98,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}I, Liú Bèi, have long admired your exalted brilliance, sir Sleeping Dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.06,0:03:10.92,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}Twice I came to offer you my respects and twice went back empty handed. It is most regrettable.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.20,0:03:14.48,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,995.182)}{\bord14}I am a member of the imperial clan
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.48,0:03:17.64,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}and have witnessed crumbling of the dynasty and the rise of warlords.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.64,0:03:22.72,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}Sinister forces abuse the sovereign and it makes my insides split with grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.72,0:03:25.38,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}Although I have the ambition to uphold the House of Hàn—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.42,0:03:28.32,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,995.182)}{\bord14}I am truly lacking in statesmanship and grand strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.36,0:03:32.30,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,995.182)}{\bord14}I wish in your benevolence and righteousness—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.46,0:03:37.36,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}—Were you to generously use the talents of \NLǚ Wàng and carry out the brilliant plans of Zǐfáng —
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.50,0:03:41.24,Note (Potential style?),,0,0,0,,Note: Lǚ Wàng AKA. Jiāng Zǐyá was the strategist who helped establish the Zhōu Dynasty.\N Zǐfáng AKA. Zhāng Liáng was the strategist who helped establish the Hàn dynasty.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.40,0:03:41.57,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}—then the Empire and the spirits of the nation would be fortunate indeed!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.60,0:03:46.78,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}Allow me to express my intentions to you: I wish to once again purify myself—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.00,0:03:51.28,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}—so that I can personally offer my respects and to receive your teachings.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.16,0:03:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Give this letter to your brother. \NI shall take my leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.82,0:04:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a safe return, General.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.26,0:04:13.08,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,995.182)}{\bord14.318}{\i1}...The freezing northern wind at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.80,0:04:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}-The old master has arrived.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.05,0:04:21.89,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,995.182)}{\bord14.318}{\i1}...Thick, dark clouds ten thousand li away.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.69,0:04:30.03,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,995.182)}{\bord14.318}{\i1}In the vast sky snow disorderly flutters.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.27,0:04:37.93,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,995.182)}{\bord14.318}{\i1}The mountains of old have completely changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.44,0:04:45.64,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,995.182)}{\bord14.318}{\i1}I face upward and gaze upon creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.21,0:04:53.75,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,995.182)}{\bord14.318}{\i1}Is it a fight between jade dragons?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.19,0:05:00.46,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,995.182)}{\bord14.318}{\i1}One after another, scales are flying—
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.00,0:05:07.03,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,995.182)}{\bord14.318}{\i1}—and in an instant spread all over the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.17,0:05:15.70,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,995.182)}{\bord14.318}{\i1}The mule is crossing a small bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.01,0:05:19.74,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,995.182)}{\bord14.227}{\i1}I regret alone that plum-flowers are so thin...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.11,0:05:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}-Who is this gentleman?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.08,0:05:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}My brother's father-in-law: \NMaster {\i1}Huáng Chéngyàn.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.55,0:05:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Greetings, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.70,0:05:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Lord Huáng, the lines you just recited are most inspired.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.14,0:05:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I learnt these lines of {\i1}the Liángfùyín{\i0} at my son-in-law's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.14,0:05:50.70,Note (Potential style?),,0,0,0,,Note: Liángfùyín (梁父吟) was a real folk-song from Shandong in the Han Dynasty. \NAccording to {\i1}Records,{\i0}  Zhuge Liang had a particular liking for this ballad.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.14,0:05:47.17,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\fade(255,0,255,0,420,4000,4420)\pos(265.997,592.72)}Huáng Chéngyàn
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.71,0:05:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I remembered it as I saw the plum flowers and crossed the bridge, so I started to sing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.62,0:06:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't think such an august character was listening!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.90,0:06:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear sir, have you seen your son-in-law?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.94,0:06:07.94,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\fade(255,0,255,0,420,4000,4420)\pos(235.542,694.491)}Guān Yǔ\NStyled: Yúncháng
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.40,0:06:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I also came to visit him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.00,0:07:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, four days from now is a most auspicious day!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.60,0:07:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You should part then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.22,0:08:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Excellent, excellent!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.20,0:08:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I will fast for three days starting now \Nso as to purify myself for this meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.31,0:08:09.20,Note (Potential style?),,0,0,0,,Note: Part of old Zhōu etiquette and ritual, as an utmost show of respect and reverence to someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.38,0:08:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll then go to Wòlóng-Ridge to visit Kǒngmíng.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.92,0:08:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,No need to accompany me further, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.32,0:08:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,No need.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.10,0:08:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a safe trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.68,0:08:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother, I have held back \Nthe other two times.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.34,0:08:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But now I must speak my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.88,0:08:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You have personally visited Kǒngmíng at Wòlóng-Ridge twice already.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.05,0:08:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The favor you show him is too great.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.09,0:08:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid that Zhūgě Liàng fellow's reputation is but an empty one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.30,0:08:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,—That's why he's avoiding you \Nand doesn't dare meet with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.98,0:08:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother, you're familiar with {\i1}the Spring and Autumn Annals.{\i0} You should know!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.74,0:09:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,In ancient times, before meeting the Commoner East of the Walls, Duke Huán of Qí had to go five times!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.90,0:09:03.50,Note (Potential style?),,0,0,0,,Note: Duke Huán of Qí was the first of the Five-Hegemons in the Spring and Autumn period.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.55,0:09:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,How could it be less for me when I want to meet such a great talent of our age?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.18,0:09:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need to go there personally, brother. \NI will bring him here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.72,0:09:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Servants! Ready my horse and bring me some rope. I'm going to Wòlóng-Ridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.36,0:09:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.92,0:09:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.68,0:09:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.92,0:09:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.32,0:09:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.83,0:09:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother, what are you going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.76,0:09:30.94,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\fade(255,0,255,0,420,4000,4420)\pos(1185.359,753.856)}Zhang Fei \NStyled: Yide
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.84,0:09:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to get Sleeping Dragon here on your behalf, elder brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.40,0:09:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And {\i1}how{\i0} will you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.20,0:09:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,If he doesn't come, I will use this rope \Nto bring him here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.02,0:09:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Third brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.20,0:09:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you wish to ruin everything for me!?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.89,0:09:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord14.318}It is because Cáo Cāo has so many strategists, could he defeat Yuan Shao.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.00,0:10:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1043.182)}{\bord14}That Sun Quan can command the lands of Jiangdong is thanks to the talents he has acquired.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.53,0:10:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1043.182)}{\bord14}They will surely become hegemons.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.68,0:10:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}But I depend on Liu Biao, condemned to be entrenched a tiny place such as Xinye.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.36,0:10:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}All this because I lack a great gentleman by my side who can administer stratagems and cultivate armies.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.14,0:10:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1043.182)}{\bord14}You are like my brother. We live and die together, yet—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.66,0:10:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,995.182)}{\bord14}—how could you still distort all that I care for...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.59,0:10:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Elder brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.35,0:10:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Elder brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.64,0:10:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}Have you not heard the story of how King Wen of Zhou visited Jiang Ziya?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.37,0:10:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}If even King Wen had to be so respectful, why do you intend to be this barbaric?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.84,0:10:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1043.182)}{\bord14}You will not go. \NI shall go with Yunchang.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.44,0:10:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.24,0:10:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Since you are both going, brothers, how can I stay behind?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.55,0:10:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Elder brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.06,0:11:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,If you come with us, you must not be rude under any circumstance.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.30,0:11:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand, Elder Brother, I understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.15,0:12:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir Zhūgě Jun, is your brother at home?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.28,0:12:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,He arrived at dusk yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.06,0:12:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You may meet with him today, General.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.54,0:12:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Many thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.86,0:12:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,How insolent! Why not just lead us inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.98,0:12:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He just waved his hands and left!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.96,0:12:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Each has their own matters. \NWe shouldn't step out of line.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.82,0:12:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I already told you. Mind your manners.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.09,0:12:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood, Elder Brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.62,0:13:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So you visit again, General Liú?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.78,0:13:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,May I trouble you to tell your master that Liú Bèi has arrived to pay his respects?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.78,0:13:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The master is at home, but he is taking a nap in the thatched cottage.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.60,0:14:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Since that's the case, don't call him yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.87,0:14:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers, wait outside for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.34,0:14:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The master is sleeping,\N we shouldn't disturb him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.96,0:14:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,This way, General.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.31,0:14:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you wait inside, General?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.91,0:14:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I will wait until the master is awake.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.83,0:15:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Third brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.83,0:15:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The arrogance of this man!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.63,0:15:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Our brother is at his porch, and he's still {\i1}sleeping!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.92,0:15:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,-Third Brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.24,0:15:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll burn the cottage down, \Nsee if he still sleeps then!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.74,0:15:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Third Brother! Third Brother! Third Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.91,0:15:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Third Brother, you boor!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.00,0:15:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Third Brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.80,0:16:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I will go wake the master.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.00,0:16:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not disturb him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.86,0:16:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,As you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.70,0:17:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord14\i1} Whom can wake one's dream, \Nall life have I known.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.17,0:17:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord14\i1} Long has spring-sleep last, \Ndays go slowly past.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.35,0:17:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Are there any visitors?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.12,0:17:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Imperial Uncle Liú has been waiting outside for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.48,0:17:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you tell me sooner? \NLet me change my clothes and meet him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.64,0:18:10.15,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\fade(255,0,255,0,420,4000,4420)\pos(1201.361,368.765)}Zhūgě Liàng \NStyled: Kǒngmíng
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.90,0:18:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I am a lowly member of the imperial house from Zhuó-county.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.80,0:18:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,For so long have I heard of your name, that echoes like thunder. Twice I came but we couldn't meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.47,0:18:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I left a letter, though I don't know if you've read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.25,0:18:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I am but a rural man of Nányáng.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.50,0:18:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't deserve the honor of being blessed by your presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.58,0:18:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,After you, General.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.00,0:18:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.55,0:18:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait here, brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.90,0:19:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I have already read your letter, General.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.46,0:19:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,One can perceive your worries for the state and the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.56,0:19:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,However, I regret to say that I have but meager ability. You are asking advice from a lesser man.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.51,0:19:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You were recommended by master Water Mirror \Nand Xú Yuánzhí. How could theirs be empty praise?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.45,0:19:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you don't abandon me, unworthy as I am, and offer me your guidance.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.32,0:19:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Decao and Yuanzhi are both exalted scholars of our age.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.32,0:19:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I am but a common tiller of soil. How can I discuss matters of state?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.56,0:19:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would you throw away a fine jade to look for a rough stone?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.84,0:19:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,995.182)}{\pos(726.136,1043.182)}{\bord14}You are too modest.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.28,0:19:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1043.182)}{\bord14}Worthy men wish to command the talents of this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.18,0:19:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1043.182)}{\bord14}How could one idle away life in these secluded groves?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.41,0:19:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1043.182)}{\bord14}I hope you can consider the living souls of the Empire and free me of ignorance and folly
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.00,0:20:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1043.182)}{\bord14}Since you insist, I will hear you, General.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.87,0:20:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1043.182)}{\bord14}The Hàn Empire is collapsing \Nand treacherous ministers are in power.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.55,0:20:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1043.182)}{\bord14}I have no power, but I wish to extend justice all over the realm.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.78,0:20:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1043.182)}{\bord14}However, I am lacking in strategy and my achievement inadequate.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.45,0:20:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}{\pos(726.136,1043.182)}If sir could be so gracious \Nand help us from this calamity...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.13,0:20:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,995.182)}{\bord14}We would be most fortunate!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.83,0:20:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}Ever since the treachery of Dong Zhuo, \Nmany champions of our time rose up in arms.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.41,0:20:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}Cáo Cāo's strength couldn't compare with that of Yuan Shao's —
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.91,0:20:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,995.182)}{\bord14}— yet he was the man to defeat Yuan Shao.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.16,0:20:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}Not only was this for proper timing, but he also benefited from others' cunning.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.75,0:21:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,995.182)}{\bord14}Now, Cáo Cāo has a million men—
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.93,0:21:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}—and overturns the Son of Heaven to command over the lords. We cannot fight him for supremacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.08,0:21:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}Sun Quan rules Jiangdong, where his family has had ties for three generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.74,0:21:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,995.182)}{\bord14}A prosperous land that's difficult to enter.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.88,0:21:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}He can be used for support, \Nbut must not to be conspired against.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.45,0:21:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}Jing-Province borders the Han- and Mian-Rivers to the north —
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.88,0:21:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,995.182)}{\bord14}—and gives access to the Southern Sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.88,0:21:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}In the east, ally with Wu. \NIn the west, reach the region of Bāshǔ.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.08,0:21:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}Military force is to be used there,\N for their lord is unable to keep them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.92,0:21:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,995.182)}{\bord14}For Heaven has granted you that land, General.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.86,0:21:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,995.182)}{\bord14}Does the general not intend to take it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.77,0:21:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,995.182)}{\bord14}To the west of Jīng-Province, there is{\i1} Yì-Province.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.18,0:21:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}The roads are difficult, but the land is rich for a thousand lǐ.  Heaven's storehouse!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.22,0:21:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord13}It's because of this did {\i1}the High Forefather {\i0}accomplish his imperial designs.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.28,0:21:58.46,Note (Potential style?),,0,0,0,,Note: Hàn Gāozǔ AKA. Liu Bang
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.54,0:22:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,995.182)}{\bord14}But its lord, {\i1}Liú Zhang{\i0}, is dim-witted and weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.60,0:22:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}Even though his land is wealthy,\N he can't support his people and army.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.85,0:22:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,995.182)}{\bord14}Therefore, its talents long for an enlightened ruler.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.89,0:22:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,995.182)}{\bord14}You are a member of the imperial clan, General.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.26,0:22:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}Your noble intent is well-known, \Nand heroes all over desire a virtuous leader.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.40,0:22:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}If you can conquer Jing- and Yì-Provinces, fortify its natural barriers —
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.10,0:22:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}— make peace with western Rong-tribes, calm the southern Yí and Yuè —
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.90,0:22:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}— ally with the eastern Wú, \Nand reform the constitution within!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.36,0:22:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}When the moment is right, send finest generals with the army of Jīng towards Rivers Yuan and Luo —
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.40,0:22:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}— while you lead the armies of Yì-Province \Nand attack from the Qínchuān.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.52,0:22:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}Then, how could the people not welcome your armies with food and drink, General?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.00,0:22:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}If you proceed as I just said, you can accomplish your grand design—
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.56,0:22:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,995.182)}{\bord14}—and the Hàn Dynasty can be restored.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.80,0:22:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,995.182)}{\bord14}You wish to build your great cause, General—
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.98,0:22:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}—then let Cáo Cāo dominate the north \Nand Sun Quan have the shelter of the south.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.98,0:23:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}While you, general, will have the support of the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.38,0:23:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}This is a map of the fifty-four counties of the western regions.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.84,0:23:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}First take Jīng-Province as your home, then seize Yì-Province as your base —
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.54,0:23:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,995.182)}{\bord14}—  to form the legs of a crucible.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.54,0:23:17.70,Note (Potential style?),,0,0,0,,Note: Referring to a "Dǐng (鼎)"-ritual vessel, a Zhou-era symbol for power.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.30,0:23:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,995.182)}{\bord14}After that, you can aim for the Central Plains.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.16,0:23:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,995.182)}{\bord14}This is the grand strategy I present to you, General.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.77,0:23:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,With just a few words you have opened my eyes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.91,0:23:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as if I can see the blue skies cleared from the dark clouds.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.41,0:23:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.18,0:23:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Liú Biao of Jīng and Liú Zhāng of Yì are both members of the imperial family.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.16,0:23:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,How could I bring myself to overthrow them?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.36,0:23:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,As I have observed, and Liú Biao won't be in this world for long.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.50,0:24:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Liú Zhang isn't a man of great drives, and after some time, the western regions will be yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.98,0:24:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Without leaving this cottage, sir has already known the land will be split into three!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.58,0:24:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,None throughout the ages can compare!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.98,0:24:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Though my name be of small repute,\N my virtue meagre —
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.00,0:24:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,— I hope sir does not resent to offer me help. I will listen most reverently to your advice!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.56,0:24:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I have long been content tilling the land without any worry for this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.96,0:24:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot accept.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.10,0:24:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, will you really not leave the mountains and aid us?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.31,0:24:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I fear I cannot accept.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.95,0:24:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,If sir won't leave their retreat, \Nwhat is left anymore for the people?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.95,0:24:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,If sir won't leave their retreat, \Nwhat will become of the people?!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.56,0:25:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,To realize the general's dream, I, Zhūgé Liàng, will vow to serve you with utmost loyalty.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.36,0:26:05.25,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}With his hair tied, learning, \Ncultivating virtue and character.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.18,0:26:05.25,Song,,0,0,0,,{\k80}Shù {\k60}fǎ {\k51}dú {\k45}shī {\k73}shū,{\k40} xiū {\k52}dé {\k84}jiān {\k143}xiū {\k36}shēn{\k120}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.36,0:26:12.43,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}He gazes up in the sky and down to his books, stratagems in his mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.28,0:26:12.49,Song,,0,0,0,,{\k58}Yǎng {\k66}guān {\k29}yǔ {\k53}fǔ{\k186}chá, {\k37}tāo{\k81}lüè {\k44}xiōng{\k51}zhōng {\k50}cún{\k0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.60,0:26:20.56,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\bord14}Though he's tilling the land, \Nforget does he not the troubles of the nation.
